{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-template-js","path":"/wooden die/","result":{"pageContext":{"id":"94bba106-3711-5a3d-9dbb-f05f88706cd6","html":"<p><em>march 2026</em></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/afef0/dice-done-one.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"a wooden die\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/1c72d/dice-done-one.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/a80bd/dice-done-one.jpg 148w,\n/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/1c91a/dice-done-one.jpg 295w,\n/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/1c72d/dice-done-one.jpg 590w,\n/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/a8a14/dice-done-one.jpg 885w,\n/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/fbd2c/dice-done-one.jpg 1180w,\n/static/92962def290a16d9c7d52fa3a6170c81/afef0/dice-done-one.jpg 4624w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>made this using some leftover wood as a birthday gift for a friend. the main body is a square walnut dowel that i cut and sanded more or less to a cube, and the pips are a cherry dowel that i carved to the right thickness and jammed in with superglue.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/d3c45/dice-wip-dowel.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"die with dowels sticking out of it\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/1c72d/dice-wip-dowel.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/a80bd/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 148w,\n/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/1c91a/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 295w,\n/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/1c72d/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 590w,\n/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/a8a14/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 885w,\n/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/fbd2c/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 1180w,\n/static/511af7645b7b26b0860ef34d39be315b/d3c45/dice-wip-dowel.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i had some tear out while drilling the holes on this side. fortunately i was able to recover by mixing some superglue and walnut sawdust and using that to fill the gap back up after i had glued each sides' pips in.</p>\n<p>unfortunately, said tear out also meant that the drill bit slipped into my thumb, which did make a moderate cut. hence the tape used as bandage:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/d3c45/dice-wip-hand.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"the dice before finish was applied\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/1c72d/dice-wip-hand.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/a80bd/dice-wip-hand.jpg 148w,\n/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/1c91a/dice-wip-hand.jpg 295w,\n/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/1c72d/dice-wip-hand.jpg 590w,\n/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/a8a14/dice-wip-hand.jpg 885w,\n/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/fbd2c/dice-wip-hand.jpg 1180w,\n/static/d6a3c09445c6a42dfd8a0888569a711d/d3c45/dice-wip-hand.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>i finished with some wax that i had leftover as well. turned out cool! i did test it with 100 rolls to see how fair it was and it was actually not <em>too</em> bad - 3s and 5s came in at roughly 13% which supposedly was just within the bounds of \"fair\" according to the website that i did this on.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/d3c45/dice-done-two.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 133.1081081081081%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"the finished dice held aloft\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/1c72d/dice-done-two.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/a80bd/dice-done-two.jpg 148w,\n/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/1c91a/dice-done-two.jpg 295w,\n/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/1c72d/dice-done-two.jpg 590w,\n/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/a8a14/dice-done-two.jpg 885w,\n/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/fbd2c/dice-done-two.jpg 1180w,\n/static/88d1d5a2b1e516d96d7811ca8422f7bc/d3c45/dice-done-two.jpg 3472w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>"}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}